---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="render_pipeline — ArchLens"
  description="Stitch multiple data-flow paths into one end-to-end Mermaid pipeline diagram across entrypoint boundaries."
>
  <section class="tool-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-page-header">
        <h1 class="tool-page-title">render_pipeline</h1>
        <span class="tool-page-badge">Query</span>
      </div>

      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        Where <code>call_flow</code> shows the call chain for a single entrypoint and
        <code>trace_data_flow</code> produces textual per-path output,
        <code>render_pipeline</code> follows <code>linkedPathIds</code> through the workflow
        linker to stitch multiple paths into one connected Mermaid diagram. Use it when the
        question is "what does the full pipeline look like across brokers, shared state, or
        persistence handoffs?" Requires <code>index_workspace</code> first; chain quality
        depends on resolved channel names and field names in source.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Arguments</h2>
      <table class="arg-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Name</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>entrypointName</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Filter chains whose root entrypoint name or path contains this substring. Prefix with verb: <code>"POST /orders"</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>channel</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Filter chains passing through a messaging link whose channel name contains this substring.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>maxDepth</td>
            <td>integer</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Maximum pipeline segments per chain. Default: <code>8</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>maxChains</td>
            <td>integer</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Maximum distinct chains in one response. Default: <code>5</code>.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Example</h2>
      <div class="terminal-card">
        <div class="terminal-top">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span>
          <strong>tools/call</strong>
        </div>
        <pre><code>{`{
  "name": "render_pipeline",
  "arguments": {
    "channel": "order-events",
    "maxDepth": 6
  }
}`}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Output</h2>
      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        One Mermaid <code>flowchart TD</code> per pipeline chain, with segments separated by
        boundary nodes: cylinders for shared-state stores, rounded rectangles for message
        broker channels, circles for event buses. When no chains are found, a diagnostic
        message reports counts for data-flow paths, linked sinks, messaging sinks,
        unresolved destinations, and persistence reads and writes — use these to identify
        what config or extraction data is missing. The response's <code>structuredContent</code>
        carries a <code>{"{ diagramType: \"mermaid\" }"}</code> marker alongside the diagram text.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Related tools</h2>
      <div class="related-pills">
        <a href="/tools/trace-data-flow" class="related-pill">trace_data_flow</a>
        <a href="/#tools" class="related-pill">call_flow</a>
        <a href="/tools/query-architecture-graph" class="related-pill">query_architecture_graph</a>
        <a href="/tools/index-workspace" class="related-pill">index_workspace</a>
      </div>

      <a href="/#tools" class="tool-back-link">← All tools</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
